d 'FENCODE': module to provide frequency-based encoding of string and numeric variables
d
d   fencode provides frequency-based encoding of string and numeric
d variables. Unlike encode which assigns codes alphabetically,
d fencode assigns numeric codes ordered by frequency (descending or
d ascending). The command accepts both string variables and labeled
d numeric variables with non-sequential codes, standardizing them
d to sequential order. This functionality is particularly valuable
d for creating tables and graphs where frequency ordering improves
d interpretability, and for regression analysis where the most
d frequent category serves as a more meaningful base category. 
d
d KW: data management
d KW: frequencies
d
d Requires: Stata version 14
d
d Distribution-Date: 20250903
d
d Author:   Kabira Namit,  World Bank
d Support: email   knamit@@worldbank.org
d
